detaileddescription.para: The returned vector will have the same length as the SIMD width.

briefdescription.para: Return floating-point SIMD value from std::vector<real>.

detaileddescription.para: If the vector is longer than SIMD width, only the first elements will be used. If it is shorter, the contents will be repeated to fill the SIMD register.

briefdescription.para: Set SIMD register contents from three real values.

detaileddescription.para: Our reason for using three values is that 3 is not a factor in any known SIMD width, so this way there will not be any simple repeated patterns e.g. between the low/high 64/128/256 bits in the SIMD register, which could hide bugs.

briefdescription.para: Set SIMD register contents from single real value.

detaileddescription.para: All elements is set from the given value. This is effectively the same operation as simdSet1(), but is implemented using only load/store operations that have been tested separately in the bootstrapping tests.
The returned vector will have the same length as the SIMD width.

briefdescription.para: Return 32-bit integer SIMD value from std::vector<int>.

detaileddescription.para: If the vector is longer than SIMD width, only the first elements will be used. If it is shorter, the contents will be repeated to fill the SIMD register.

briefdescription.para: Set SIMD register contents from three int values.

detaileddescription.para: Our reason for using three values is that 3 is not a factor in any known SIMD width, so this way there will not be any simple repeated patterns e.g. between the low/high 64/128/256 bits in the SIMD register, which could hide bugs.

briefdescription.para: Set SIMD register contents from single integer value.

detaileddescription.para: All elements is set from the given value. This is effectively the same operation as simdSet1I(), but is implemented using only load/store operations that have been tested separately in the bootstrapping tests.
The returned vector will have the same length as the SIMD4 width.

briefdescription.para: Return floating-point SIMD4 value from std::vector<real>.

detaileddescription.para: If the vector is longer than SIMD4 width, only the first elements will be used. If it is shorter, the contents will be repeated to fill the SIMD4 register.

briefdescription.para: Set SIMD4 register contents from three real values.

detaileddescription.para: It might seem stupid to use three values when we know that the SIMD4 width is 4, but it simplifies the test organization when the SIMD and SIMD4 tests are completely symmetric.

briefdescription.para: Set SIMD4 register contents from single real value.

detaileddescription.para: All elements is set from the given value. This is effectively the same operation as simd4Set1(), but is implemented using only load/store operations that have been tested separately in the bootstrapping tests.
